    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-09-16T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-09-16T12:00:00-05:00" n="404"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">310.2/9–1652: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gifford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-09-16T18:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 16, 1952—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1533. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> pass <gloss target="#t_USUN1"
                        >USUN</gloss> New York. Re Chinese representation <gloss target="#t_FonOff1"
                        >FonOff</gloss> anticipates no difficulty United States–<gloss
                        target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> delegates working out necessary formulae at New
                    York in view fact <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss>’s views as set forth in
                    tel 1815, Sept 12 (110 to <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> September 8)
                    appear to <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> to be in line with “moratorium
                    understanding” this question.</p>
                <p>In course conversation <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> mentioned its
                    concern with Chinese representative question in relation to <gloss
                        target="#t_WHO1">WHO</gloss>. <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> believes
                    that concurrence in its readmission to and reassessment its share of <gloss
                        target="#t_WHO1">WHO</gloss> could be interpreted as implying recognition
                    Chinese Nationalist Government which <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss> wishes to
                    avoid. Point is evidently worrying <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>,
                    particularly fact <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> is actively supporting
                    Chinese Nationalists.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gifford</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
